cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI

This paper deals with natural language processing and historical analysis of a large corpus of written Arabic language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for periodization, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of NLP tools for processing the corpus could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
